This was so cute to present! I didn't follow this risotto recipe, though (yuck). For better pumpkin risotto saute about 2 generous cups shallots with a couple cloves of garlic in butter, then add the rice, then some dry white wine, wait for the wine to aborb, then add pumpkin/squash plus a pinch of nutmeg, then start adding the broth (definitely no water!), a little at a time, until all broth is gone except for about a half cup (approx. 15-20 min.) Remove from heat, add parm. chz, remaining liquid, S and P, and let stand for a few minutes. Much better!

