Rating: 3
I am a busy mom of a three year old and a 5 month old. Needless to say I am always trying to save. So with that in mind, the evening before my beautiful adult dinner, I cooked the pumpkins for 30 minutes. Removed the seeds and allowed them to cool completely. During this time I made the Risotto exactly as the recipe called for except for par boiling the diced pumpkin. ( a mistake that worked to my advantage) After the risotto cooled I added the diced pumpkin. Once everything was cold, I filled the pumpkins with the risotto, wrapped them up in their roasting pan with tin foil. The following evening I simply put them in the oven at 400 for about 30 minutes and served. I was truley skeptical that I had ruined this dish, but the risotto was still firm, moist, and the pumpkin ever so slightly crisp. I will definately do this again.

